    <h2 style="text-align:center">Semantic UI</h2>
    <h3 style="text-align:center">Text</h3>
    <p>
        Text can be colored or resized using the text class. Note: Only usable within &lt;span&gt; tags
		<br><br>
		<h4>Colour</h4>
			Syntax goes in the format: &lt;span class="ui <i>colour</i> text"&gt<i>The text you want formatted</i>&lt;/span&gt;<br><br>
			Ex: 
			<code>
				This is &lt;span class="ui red text"&gt;red&lt;/span&gt; text and this is &lt;span class="ui blue text"&gt;blue&lt;/span&gt; text 
				and this is &lt;span class="ui purple text"&gt;purple&lt;/span&gt; text
			</code>
		<br><br>
		The code above has the following output: <br> <br>
		<div style="font-weight: bold">
			This is <span class="ui red text">red</span> text and this is <span class="ui blue text">blue</span> 
			text and this is <span class="ui purple text">purple</span> text
		</div><br><br>
		<br>
		<h4>Size</h4>
		Syntax goes in the format: &lt;span class="ui <i>size</i> text"&gt;<i>The text you want formatted</i>&lt;/span&gt<br><br>
		Ex: 
		<code>
			This is &lt;span class="ui small text"&gt;small text&lt;/span&gt;<br><br>
			This is &lt;span class="ui medium text"&gt;medium text&lt;/span&gt;<br><br>
			This is &lt;span class="ui large text"&gt;large text&lt;/span&gt;<br><br>
		</code>
		<br><br>
		The code above has the following output: <br><br><br>
		This is <span class="ui small text">small text</span><br><br>
		This is <span class="ui medium text">medium text</span><br><br>
		This is <span class="ui large text">large text</span><br><br>
	</p>
